- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes a computational methodology for integrating CAD and numerical analysis, which falls under the scope of computational engineering. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper focuses on the Finite Cell Method (FCM), which is a numerical method for solving partial differential equations, and proposes a new algorithm for point membership classification. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper deals with handling "dirty geometries" in CAD models, which involves geometric algorithms for identifying the inside-outside state of integration points. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper may also be relevant to computer graphics, as it deals with geometric modeling and visualization. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper proposes a new algorithm for point membership classification, which may be of interest to researchers developing mathematical software for numerical analysis.
